column6: Gucci Vintage Monochrome Blue Floral Silk Scarf Flora 1966 Accornero
column7: The Flora silk scarf born in 1966 by the artist Vittorio Accornero. He was the textile designer for Gucci between the 1960s and 1981. The Flora design is a magical and delicate composition of flowers, berries and insects depicted with the precision of a naturalist, in 37 vibrant colors on a white background. The 9 bouquets represented contain: lilies, ivy, poppies, cornflowers, daffodils, buttercups, anemones, tulips, irises and among these, butterflies, dragonflies, wasps, grasshoppers and beetles. - Title: 'Flora'- Designed by Vittorio Accornero for GUCCI in 1966 - Monochrome blue floral design on white background - 100% Silk - Printed GUCCI signature, 'V.Accornero' signature printed on the scarf.
